---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "W++ FAQ - Questions Nobody Asked, But We Answered";
const description = "Everything you never needed to know about W++, including Visual Basic hatred, plugins, and the truth behind OOPSIE.";
const ogImage = "https://w-plus-plus.vercel.app/wpp-logo.png";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} ogImage={ogImage}>
  <section class="faq">
    <h1>❓ Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

    <details>
      <summary>🤔 Why is it called W++?</summary>
      <p>
        I took the name from the gaming world — <strong>W</strong> means a "win", so <strong>W++</strong> means "win++" — always stacking Ws.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>🦥 What does OOPSIE stand for?</summary>
      <p>
        <strong>Object-Oriented Programming Sometimes Isn’t Excellent.</strong>
        A philosophy. A lifestyle. A mistake turned into a framework.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>💥 Is W++ production-ready?</summary>
      <p>
        Only if your production environment thrives on chaos and irony.
        For real-world use, consult your inner sloth.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>🐞 What if I find a bug?</summary>
      <p>
        Congratulations! You just became a core contributor. Please open an issue (or a meme) on GitHub.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>🚫 Is it compatible with Visual Basic?</summary>
      <p>
        No. And we’re proud of that.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>🛠️ Can I extend W++ with plugins?</summary>
      <p>
        Yes! Write your plugin in C#, or summon an entity that alters reality.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>📦 How is W++ installed?</summary>
      <p>
        Use the <code>ingot</code> CLI or the GUI installer. For advanced souls, build from source with .NET.
        Full instructions on the <a href="/">homepage</a>.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>🎭 Is this a joke?</summary>
      <p>
        We like to take life in a humorous way — but the language works. Mostly.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>🧠 Does it support AI?</summary>
      <p>
        Of course! The W++ installer comes with a baked-in <strong>Annoying Intelligence™</strong>.
      </p>
    </details>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .faq {
  max-width: 800px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 2rem;
  background: #2b2b2b;
  border-radius: 10px;
}

h1 {
  text-align: center;
  color: #ffa500;
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
  font-size: 1.8rem;
}

details {
  background: #1e1e1e;
  padding: 1rem;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  border-radius: 8px;
  cursor: pointer;
  font-size: 1rem;
}

summary {
  font-weight: bold;
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  color: #ffa500;
  outline: none;
}

p {
  color: #ccc;
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
  font-size: 0.95rem;
}

/* 📱 Responsive tweaks */
@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .faq {
    padding: 1.2rem 1rem;
    margin: 1rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  summary {
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  details {
    padding: 0.8rem;
  }
}

</style>
